sentences.sentence: Published 6:42 pm Tuesday, December 12, 2023ByLetters to the EditorDear Editor,I would like to thank the 14,218 citizens in the 89th district who believed in my candidacy and voted for me in the November election.
I am so proud that my race for delegate for the 89th District was run with honesty, dignity, and integrity.

Thank you to my team and others who worked tirelessly from the beginning to the end… I strongly believe that a candidate should focus on their experiences and qualifications and set priorities that benefit all people.
Rest assured, I have never needed a position or title to serve and fight for you.
My heart and passion to serve is not predicated on what title and position I hold but because I know my purpose.
